content:
With a lot of help from Alec, I updated to sd3.1.4 and have now succeeded in building JavaScript v2.0.1 tagged v2.0.1j
It has been pulled into the catalogue and I have been able to install it that way. Great :smile:
However, I have discovered the builds are in the alpha repository - not prod :grimacing:
It was definitely tagged correctly - I can see the tag 6ea90e5 in my plugin repositary.
I find them in prod. Installed fine from an update of the catalog. Thanks for sticking with it.

Some production builds under sd3.1.4 still going into the alpha repository.
Most builds go into my production repository as expected.
However, some debian builds still go into alpha . See screenshot Alpha-repository.png
